<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/178> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #178" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.3.6-7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/174> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #174" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.2.1; Diod. 11.75.1; Fast. Cap. (Sp. Postumius A. f. P. n. Albus Regi [- - -]); Dion. Hal. 9.60.1; Chr. 354 (Rigilliense et Prisco II); Fast. Hyd. (Regilliano et Fusco), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 24f., 91, 358f. Servilius held command against the Aequi (Liv. 3.2.1; Dion. Hal. 9.60.7), while Postumius dedicated the temple of the Dius Fidius (Dion. Hal. 9.60.8; cf. Ovid Fasti 6.213-8; CIL 1\n     , p. 319). On Postumius, see Lübker, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/173> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #173" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Servilius, see 468. The cognomen Structus may not have appeared in Fast. Cap. for 468 or 466 (Degrassi 91). The name of Postumius is preserved almost in full in Fast. Cap. I have listed them in the order given by Liv. and Diod.; the reverse order appears in Dion. Hal. and Fast. Cap." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/169> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #169" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.64.1; Diod. 11.71.1; Dion. Hal. 9.57.1; Chr. 354 (Barbato II et Volsco); Fast. Hyd. (Capitolino II et Prisco); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 91, 358f. Servilius held command against the Sabines, Quinctius against the Volscians, and captured Antium (Liv. 2.64.3-65.7; Dion. Hal. 9.57.2-58.8; Frontin. Str. 2.7.10; 2.12.1; 3.1.1); and celebrated a triumph (Dion. Hal. 9.58.8; cf. Act. Tr., Degrassi 66f., 537). On Quinctius, see Lübker, no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/167> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #167" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Quinctius' name see 471, Consuls; on that of Servilius, see above. Diod. preserves the cognomen Structus, which may not have appeared in Fast. Cap. at all (Degrassi 91)." .
